quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  12,79,"He said, 'God forbid that we should take any other but him in whose possession we found the goods; for if we did so, we would be evildoers"
  12,80,"When they despaired of moving him, they conferred privily apart. Said the eldest of them, 'Do you not know how your father has taken a solemn pledge from you by God, and aforetime you failed regarding Joseph? Never will I quit this land, until my father gives me leave, or God judges in my favour; He is the best of judges"
  12,81,"Return you all to your father, and say, \"Father, thy son stole; we do not testify except that we know; we were no guardians of the Unseen"
  12,82,"Enquire of the city wherein we were, and the caravan in which we approached; surely we are truthful men"
  12,83,"No!' he said 'But your spirits tempted you to do somewhat. But come, sweet patience! Haply God will bring them all to me; He is the All-knowing, the All-wise"
  12,84,"And he turned away from them, and said, 'Ah, woe is me for Joseph!' And his eyes turned white because of the sorrow that he choked within him"
  12,85,"By God,' they said, 'thou wilt never cease mentioning Joseph till thou art consumed, or among the perishing"
  12,86,"He said, 'I make complaint of my anguish and my sorrow unto God; I know from God that you know not"